<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-20] document separate MGS as preferred configuration for IR</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-20</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-15&quot; title=&quot;Recommend separate MGT device on backup MDS node&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-15&quot;&gt;LUDOC-15&lt;/a&gt; is for updating the manual to recommend separate MGS for new filesystem configurations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For IR we need to document a process to move an existing MGS from a shared MDS filesystem to a separate filesystem (this may already be done?).  This can be done in the manual first, since it is not specific to IR.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Document IR user tuneables, what they mean, how they are expected to be used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Document new IR recovery mechanisms.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
